quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  43,57,"And when the son of Mary was set forth as a parable, behold thy people turned away from him"
  43,58,"and said, 'Are our gods better, or is he?' They did not set it forth to thee save for wrangling. Nay, but they are a contentious people"
  43,59,"He is but a servant whom we have been gracious to, and we have made him an example for the children of Israel"
  43,60,And if we please we can make of you angels in the earth to succeed you
  43,61,"And, verily, he is a sign of the Hour. Doubt not then concerning it, but follow this right way"
  43,62,"and let not the devil turn you away; verily, he is to you an open foe"
  43,63,"And when Jesus came with manifest signs he said, 'I am come to you with wisdom, and I will explain to you something of that whereon ye did dispute, then fear God, obey me"
  43,64,"verily, God, He is my Lord and your Lord, serve Him then, this is the right way"
  43,65,But the confederates disputed amongst themselves; and woe to those who are unjust from the torment of a grievous day
  43,66,Do they expect aught but that the Hour will come upon them suddenly while they do not perceive
  43,67,"Friends on that day shall be foes to each other, save those who fear"